                <note rend="inline" type="source">760j.6715/40</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The British Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Geddes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-08-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 6, 1920</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 491</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honour, on instructions from my
                    Government, to enquire whether the President’s decision as to the boundaries of
                    Armenia, may be expected in the near future.</p>
                <p>I understand that this question has become a matter of urgency owing to the
                    imminent signature to the Peace Treaty with Turkey, the execution of which in
                    part, at least, depends on the President’s decision.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>(For H. M. Ambassador)<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Maurice Peterson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
